Sessions 6 & 7 (VPN + pfSense + UTM) are high-weight, high-trap areas in CCEE, especially protocol differences, VPN types, authentication methods, and deployment scenarios.

Below are 30 exam-oriented MCQs (10 Basic + 10 Intermediate + 10 Advanced) covering Sessions 6 & 7 + Labs 9â€“12, aligned to CDAC PG-DITISS August 2025.

Network Defense & Countermeasures â€“ Sessions 6 & 7
BASIC MCQs (1â€“10)
1. A VPN primarily provides:
A. Faster internet
B. Secure communication over untrusted networks
C. Load balancing
D. Intrusion detection

2. Which VPN characteristic ensures data confidentiality?
A. Tunneling
B. Authentication
C. Encryption
D. Integrity

3. VPN tunneling means:
A. Blocking packets
B. Encapsulating one protocol inside another
C. NAT translation
D. Port forwarding

4. Which protocol is commonly used by OpenVPN?
A. IPSec only
B. SSL/TLS
C. PPTP
D. L2TP only

5. A Trusted VPN relies mainly on:
A. Encryption
B. Public internet
C. Dedicated private network
D. Certificates only

6. A Secure VPN differs from Trusted VPN because it:
A. Uses private links
B. Uses encryption over public networks
C. Has no authentication
D. Is slower always

7. Which VPN type connects two entire networks?
A. Remote Access VPN
B. Host-to-Host VPN
C. Site-to-Site VPN
D. Client VPN

8. Certificate-based authentication primarily provides:
A. Password storage
B. Strong identity verification
C. Faster speed
D. IP filtering

9. OpenVPN can operate over which transport protocols?
A. ICMP only
B. TCP and UDP
C. UDP only
D. TCP only

10. pfSense is based on which OS family?
A. Linux
B. Windows
C. BSD
D. Solaris

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11â€“20)
11. Which VPN protocol is considered weakest and deprecated?
A. IPSec
B. OpenVPN
C. PPTP
D. L2TP/IPSec

12. VPN integrity is mainly ensured using:
A. Hashing
B. Encryption
C. Tunneling
D. NAT

13. Mobile VPNs are designed mainly to handle:
A. High bandwidth
B. Changing IP addresses
C. Static routing
D. Wired networks only

14. In OpenVPN, certificates are primarily used for:
A. NAT traversal
B. Mutual authentication
C. Load balancing
D. Compression

15. Site-to-site VPN is BEST suited for:
A. Individual users
B. Branch office connectivity
C. Mobile devices
D. Web browsing

16. pfSense simplifies VPN deployment mainly by:
A. Removing encryption
B. GUI-based configuration
C. Disabling routing
D. Using cloud services

17. UTM VPN configuration integrates VPN with:
A. IDS only
B. Firewall and access control
C. Antivirus only
D. Proxy only

18. Which component is mandatory before configuring OpenVPN in pfSense?
A. IDS rules
B. Certificate Authority
C. Load balancer
D. DNS server

19. Password-based VPN authentication is considered weaker because:
A. It is slower
B. Passwords can be guessed or reused
C. It uses encryption
D. It needs certificates

20. Which VPN function prevents data interception?
A. Authentication
B. Encryption
C. Compression
D. Routing

ADVANCED MCQs (21â€“30)
21. From a security standpoint, IPSec vs OpenVPN comparison shows OpenVPN is preferred because:
A. Uses proprietary protocols
B. Works easily through NAT and firewalls
C. Has no encryption
D. Uses hardware acceleration only

22. A Trusted VPN is less secure than Secure VPN mainly because:
A. Uses certificates
B. Relies on provider trust instead of encryption
C. Is slower
D. Uses SSL

23. Combining certificate + password authentication provides:
A. Redundancy only
B. Multi-factor authentication
C. Faster connection
D. NAT traversal

24. In pfSense OpenVPN, client-specific overrides are used to:
A. Change firewall rules globally
B. Assign per-client settings
C. Disable encryption
D. Load balance VPN

25. UTM VPN reduces risk mainly by:
A. Centralizing security controls
B. Eliminating internet
C. Replacing firewall
D. Removing authentication

26. Mobile VPN failures often occur due to:
A. High CPU usage
B. IP address changes during roaming
C. Encryption strength
D. Firewall rules

27. From CCEE perspective, which VPN design BEST follows defense-in-depth?
A. VPN only
B. VPN + Firewall + UTM
C. VPN without authentication
D. Trusted VPN only

28. pfSense installation requires special care mainly because:
A. It is Windows-based
B. Wrong interface assignment can break connectivity
C. It lacks firewall features
D. It disables routing

29. UTM access control integrated with VPN allows:
A. Unrestricted access
B. Policy-based access for VPN users
C. VPN without firewall
D. Faster encryption

30. Which statement BEST matches CDAC exam philosophy?
A. VPN eliminates all network threats
B. Trusted VPN is always secure
C. VPN is a security control, not a guarantee
D. Certificates are optional

